strategy:
To beat these powerful creatures you will need a good team with high-skilled [[Knight]]s, some [[Paladin]]s and [[Mage]]s with a high [[Magic Level]]. The best way to kill them is from a distance because their [[Throwing Star]]s are weaker than their melee. [[Knight]]s with skills 90/90 and a Scrapper Arena weapon can kill them fairly easily. As with all creatures that use invisibility, stay alert with an [[exori ico]] to turn them visible again. Its attacks can be compared to a [[Giant Spider]]'s. Orc Warlords are more profitable to hunt since Orcish Axes have become sellable, and now make up the most valuable part of the loot.<br />{{JSpoiler|Orc Warlords, notably those from raids, can yield different loot:
* [[Orc Tusk]] from Orc Warlord in raids of the [[Machinery of War Quest]].
* [[Amazon Armor]], [[Amazon Helmet]] and [[Amazon Shield]] from Orc Warlord in raids on [[Femor Hills]].
}}
